    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><div n="1" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Caecilius <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>uci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>Flaccus pater <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>q</abbr><ex>uaestor</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>tr</abbr><ex>ibunus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>aug</abbr><ex>ur</ex></expan> curator <lb n="4"/>aedis Iovis <expan><abbr>faciund</abbr><ex>ae</ex></expan> </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> Petronia <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>ai</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilia</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>mater </ab></div><div n="3" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Caecilius <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>uci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>Flaccus <expan><abbr>fra</abbr><ex>ter</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/>IIIIvir <expan><abbr>i</abbr><ex>ure</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>icundo</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>aug</abbr><ex>ur</ex></expan> </ab></div><div n="4" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> <expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex>uintus</ex></expan> Caecilius <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>uci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>decur</abbr><ex>io</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/>a populo <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>aug</abbr><ex>ur</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>tr</abbr><ex>ibunus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>milit</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>praef</abbr><ex>ectus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>fa<supplied reason="lost">b</supplied>r</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> <lb n="6"/>III fieri iu<supplied reason="lost">ssit</supplied>
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Die Vorderseite der Tafel wölbt sich nach außen, so daß das Stück ehemals wohl von einem Rundbau stammt. Sie ist in 2 Teile gebrochen. Die Inschrift ist in 3 nicht klar voneinander abgesetzten Kolumnen geschrieben. (B): CIL XI 6940: Z. 13 und 14 vertauscht; Calbi, AE 1983: Z. 16: [iu]ssit. Datierung: Der Bruder des Dedikanten war IIIIvir i. d., übte dieses Amt also noch vor Augustus aus, unter dem Placentia den Status einer colonia erhielt.</p>
            </div>
